Oh, oh.
- No, no, just--

01:40.833 --> 01:43.200
- Whoa.
- [grunts]

01:43.202 --> 01:46.470
- Ahh, whoa!
- [laughing]

01:46.472 --> 01:48.338
[grunting]

01:48.340 --> 01:50.507
[exclaiming]

01:50.509 --> 01:53.810
- It's harder to walk,
but worth it.

01:53.812 --> 01:56.613
- Ah, the perfect end
to a perfect day:

01:56.615 --> 02:00.350
buying ourselves
the perfect ice cream.

02:00.352 --> 02:04.621
- So many flavors.

02:04.623 --> 02:06.957
- [yodels]

02:06.959 --> 02:07.657
- Whoo-hoo!

02:07.659 --> 02:11.761
Hmm, what brand should we buy,
HØGAN DUEP?

02:11.763 --> 02:14.965
- No, that's too fancy.

02:16.467 --> 02:17.968
both: Rocky road!

02:17.970 --> 02:19.569
- With real rocks!

02:19.571 --> 02:21.705
- Rocky road,
unlike our friendship,

02:21.707 --> 02:25.675
which is a smooth avenue
and will never have any bumps.

02:25.677 --> 02:27.244
- Bump.

02:27.879 --> 02:30.881
When did food get so ugly?

02:32.283 --> 02:36.253
"Lonely Krab Dinner for One:
Now 30% lonelier."

02:36.255 --> 02:37.988
Eee, can't believe
what they're charging

02:37.990 --> 02:40.690
for this frozen debris,
and I can't believe

02:40.692 --> 02:42.926
they're selling so much of it.

02:42.928 --> 02:46.029
But it sure is convenient.

02:47.265 --> 02:48.532
- [groans]

02:48.534 --> 02:50.267
[grunting]

02:50.269 --> 02:53.336
Can you imagine if they had
frozen Krabby Patties

02:53.338 --> 02:54.070
at the supermarket?

02:54.072 --> 02:55.272
Oh, that would be
so convenient,

02:55.274 --> 02:57.340
everyone in the world
could enjoy them.

02:57.342 --> 02:58.808
- Ooh, whoo!

02:58.810 --> 03:01.611
SpongeBob, that's
a million dollar idea

03:01.613 --> 03:04.347
that I just had that
you just said before me.

03:04.349 --> 03:05.482
[bubbling]

03:05.484 --> 03:07.350
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

03:07.352 --> 03:08.919
Hello, welcome to my commercial.

03:08.921 --> 03:12.422
Would you like the convenience
of a Krabby Patty at home,

03:12.424 --> 03:15.859
without the hassle
of going to the Krusty Krab?

03:15.861 --> 03:16.693
Well, now you can.

03:16.695 --> 03:20.497
Have delicious Krabby Patties
any time you want.

03:20.499 --> 03:22.966
They're in your grocer's
freezer section.

03:22.968 --> 03:25.569
Buy them.
I want your money!

03:25.571 --> 03:26.736
Did you get that, Pearly-girl?

03:26.738 --> 03:30.941
- Yes, Daddy,
and stop babying me!

03:31.676 --> 03:34.411
- So, Mr. Grouper,
what do you think?

03:34.413 --> 03:35.345
- Call me Don.

03:35.347 --> 03:37.948
- Oh, well, okay, Don.

03:37.950 --> 03:41.051
Will this make me rich?

03:41.053 --> 03:42.552
- Mr. Krabs,
if you wanna sell

03:42.554 --> 03:46.389
zero Krabby Patties
and wind up in the poor house,

03:46.391 --> 03:48.592
then I say
go with your commercial.

03:48.594 --> 03:50.460
- Oh.
- But if you really

03:50.462 --> 03:53.363
want to be rich,
keep your mouth shut,

03:53.365 --> 03:56.533
and listen to us, sir.

03:56.535 --> 03:58.368
- Ooh, okay.

03:58.370 --> 04:00.937
- Let me introduce you
to the team here at GGK.

04:00.939 --> 04:02.439
That's Barry Goby,
Rob Koi,

04:02.441 --> 04:03.740
and Limia with her team
from creative.

04:03.742 --> 04:07.344
Everyone, this is Mr. Krabs
and a yellow box.

04:07.346 --> 04:08.712
- Oh, uh, actually,
my name in Spon--

04:08.714 --> 04:11.648
- Let's say we give a look-see
at what we've cooked up for you.

04:11.650 --> 04:14.818
The Krabby Patty, a mainstay
of dining in Bikini Bottom

04:14.820 --> 04:17.620
for a very long time,
like an old friend,

04:17.623 --> 04:20.423
but not too old,
because research shows us

04:20.425 --> 04:21.124
old is gross.

04:21.125 --> 04:22.826
- Yes, oh, it's absolutely...
- Oh, of course...

04:22.828 --> 04:24.494
- Just gross.
- Yeah, no, it's disgusting.

04:24.496 --> 04:27.530
- Well, I don't think
old is gross.

04:27.532 --> 04:29.666
[yells]

04:29.668 --> 04:34.504
- Goo-goo, social networking,
ah, ah!

04:34.506 --> 04:35.071
- Exactly.

04:35.073 --> 04:36.906
Now, here are
some of the slogans

04:36.908 --> 04:38.441
we've been kicking around.

04:38.443 --> 04:42.379
"Krabby Patties:
Like a friend, but edible."

04:42.381 --> 04:46.883
"Krabby Patties:
The shut-in's favorite patty."

04:46.885 --> 04:49.552
And finally,
"Krabby Patties:

04:49.554 --> 04:51.121
Shove 'em in your mouth-hole!"

04:51.123 --> 04:51.821
- [burps]

04:51.823 --> 04:54.958
- Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh,
I have a slogan!

04:55.660 --> 04:56.926
Oh, uh, Krabby Patties:

04:56.928 --> 05:00.930
Taste so nice
that they taste nice.

05:00.932 --> 05:03.933
[crickets chirping]

05:03.935 --> 05:05.468
- [blows raspberry]

05:05.470 --> 05:08.405
- Let's just leave it
to the professionals, boy-o.

05:08.407 --> 05:10.006
- The thing is,
Frozen Krabby Patties

05:10.008 --> 05:11.408
are a convenience
for everyone,

05:11.410 --> 05:13.877
and we need a campaign
that says exactly that.

05:13.879 --> 05:18.148
We need a regular guy
to represent all consumers.

05:18.150 --> 05:19.449
- Me!
- Someone everyone

05:19.451 --> 05:20.550
can relate to...
- Oh, me, me!

05:20.552 --> 05:25.188
- With a face that says,
"I love Krabby Patties."

05:25.190 --> 05:25.822
- Mmm.

05:25.824 --> 05:28.725
- We find that face,
and we have our campaign.

05:28.727 --> 05:32.996
- And I've got
the perfect guy for the job.

05:32.998 --> 05:34.597
- Eee?

05:34.599 --> 05:36.800
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

05:36.802 --> 05:37.767
[ding]

05:37.769 --> 05:39.736
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:39.738 --> 05:43.473
- Krabby Patties:
They taste so nice,

05:43.475 --> 05:46.609
that they taste nice.

05:46.611 --> 05:49.612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:49.614 --> 05:51.214
- Hey, that was my slogan.

05:51.216 --> 05:52.148
- Great stuff, huh?

05:52.150 --> 05:54.451
This guy is gonna be a star.

05:54.453 --> 05:55.985
- I'm already a star.

05:55.987 --> 05:57.120
- That's the attitude.

05:57.122 --> 05:59.989
- Hey, SpongeBob,
now that I'm finished doing

05:59.991 --> 06:02.625
whatever it is I'm doing,
you wanna go play?

06:02.627 --> 06:03.793
- [gasps]
- Sorry, yellow box,

06:03.795 --> 06:06.930
Patrick has to make a personal
appearance at the mall.

06:06.932 --> 06:07.664
- I--oh...

06:07.666 --> 06:11.501
- Don, will this commercial
really help me make money?

06:11.503 --> 06:12.802
- You need to call
your bank, Krabs,

06:12.804 --> 06:16.239
because they are gonna have to
build an extra vault

06:16.241 --> 06:18.007
to hold all the extra money.

06:18.009 --> 06:21.978
- [in Southern accent]
Ooh, I do declare, Mr. Grouper,

06:21.980 --> 06:24.581
I believe I have
a case of the vapors.

06:24.583 --> 06:28.218
- I told you,
call me Don.

06:28.220 --> 06:28.852
- Don.

06:28.854 --> 06:32.856
- Of course, you could double,
maybe even triple or quadruple,

06:32.858 --> 06:36.159
that money if you...
no, forget it.

06:36.161 --> 06:37.160
- What?
Forget what?

06:37.162 --> 06:38.228
What, what?
What are you saying?

06:38.230 --> 06:40.063
- Well, we ran some numbers
and realized

06:40.065 --> 06:42.132
that you could make
a lot more money

06:42.134 --> 06:45.635
if you changed the formula.

06:45.637 --> 06:47.871
- How much "a lot more"?

06:47.873 --> 06:49.072
- A lot "a lot more."

06:49.074 --> 06:51.674
- Well, then let's
fill her up with filler!

06:51.676 --> 06:56.012
- Mr. Krabs, are you changing
the secret Krabby Patty formula?

06:56.014 --> 06:57.147
- Heh, no,
I-I can--

06:57.149 --> 06:59.115
well, it's just
a little tweak, me boy.

06:59.117 --> 06:59.983
- But what is "filler"?

06:59.985 --> 07:05.522
- Whoa, hey, this little yellow
box sure is full of questions.

07:05.524 --> 07:08.291
What do you say we go see
where the money's made?

07:08.293 --> 07:11.594
- Ho-ho, that sounds great!

07:11.596 --> 07:14.097
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

07:14.099 --> 07:15.532
<i>- Take a look around.</i>

07:15.534 --> 07:17.066
It's your dream come true.

07:17.068 --> 07:18.301
Through the wonders
of automation,

07:18.303 --> 07:20.236
this factory can make
as many Krabby Patties

07:20.238 --> 07:23.239
in one minute
as you used to make in a week.

07:23.241 --> 07:25.642
Take a whiff
of the future, Krabs.

07:25.644 --> 07:27.043
Does it smell like money?

07:27.045 --> 07:31.748
- [sniffs]
Oh, yeah.

07:32.817 --> 07:33.683
- [teeth chattering]

07:33.685 --> 07:36.319
- Hey, why does
that barrel say "sand"?

07:36.321 --> 07:37.654
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:37.656 --> 07:38.655
- Well, it's imported.

07:38.657 --> 07:42.325
It's spelled "sand,"
but it's pronounced, "filler."

07:42.327 --> 07:45.094
- Hey, let's check in on
our taste test area.

07:45.096 --> 07:47.764
- Whoa, whoa, oh!

07:47.766 --> 07:50.233
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:50.235 --> 07:52.635
- Hmm.
This tastes kind of bad.

07:52.637 --> 07:53.870
- Would you buy it, though?

07:53.872 --> 07:55.939
- Well, yeah,
for the convenience...

07:55.941 --> 07:58.241
and the face of that stupid guy.
[chuckles]

07:58.243 --> 08:02.045
Though I have noticed
a bit of a side effect.

08:02.047 --> 08:03.780
Hmm-hmm.

08:05.249 --> 08:06.950
[both grunting]
- Oh!

08:06.952 --> 08:09.152
- [laughs]
He loves it.

08:09.154 --> 08:09.953
- Great news, Krabs.

08:09.955 --> 08:12.355
Sales are going all the way up
to the surface of the ocean.

08:12.357 --> 08:14.724
Here's your first check.

08:14.726 --> 08:15.992
<i>[cash register ding]</i>

08:15.994 --> 08:16.993
- Huh?

08:16.995 --> 08:18.294
<i>[cash register ding]</i>

08:18.296 --> 08:18.995
[gasps]

08:18.997 --> 08:20.196
<i>[cash register ding]</i>

08:20.198 --> 08:21.064
[screams]

08:21.066 --> 08:22.732
Oh.
- Mr. Krabs?

08:22.734 --> 08:24.801
- I'm rich, boy-o, rich.

08:24.803 --> 08:27.704
- Great, can we go back
to the Krusty Krab now?

08:27.706 --> 08:30.173
- Yes, yes, we can.

08:30.175 --> 08:32.075
- Hooray, finally!

08:32.077 --> 08:33.710
[bubbling]

08:33.712 --> 08:37.246
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

08:37.249 --> 08:40.717
[tools clanking]

08:40.719 --> 08:42.251
[exclaiming]

08:42.254 --> 08:44.721
[scatting]

08:44.723 --> 08:45.922
- Whatcha doing, boy?

08:45.924 --> 08:46.923
- Making Krabby Patties.

08:46.925 --> 08:50.226
- Oh, no, you've made
your last Krabby Patty.

08:50.228 --> 08:52.929
- You mean my last one
for the morning rush?

08:52.931 --> 08:53.530
- No, ever.

08:53.532 --> 08:56.132
- You mean my last one
for today-ever?

08:56.134 --> 08:59.669
- No, I mean forever and ever.

08:59.671 --> 09:01.404
You're fired.
- Fired?

09:01.406 --> 09:02.772
- But I'm ready to re-hire you.

09:02.774 --> 09:05.308
- Oh, please,
re-hire me Mr. Krabs.

09:05.310 --> 09:07.110
I'll do anything.

09:07.112 --> 09:09.245
- Then follow me.

09:09.247 --> 09:12.081
[machine whirring]

09:12.383 --> 09:15.818
<i>[carnival music]</i>

09:15.820 --> 09:18.421
- [robotic voice]
This tastes nice.

09:18.423 --> 09:19.088
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:19.090 --> 09:23.026
- [robotic voice]
Ow, curses, foiled again, ow.

09:23.028 --> 09:26.729
- You turned the Krusty Krab
into some kind of museum?

09:26.731 --> 09:28.164
- That's right, me boy.

09:28.166 --> 09:30.934
It's all history now,
but you,

09:30.936 --> 09:34.270
you have
the most important job of all.

09:34.272 --> 09:36.940
You give tours
and sell tchotchkes

09:36.942 --> 09:37.774
in the gift shop.

09:37.776 --> 09:39.742
- Yeah, but what if someone
wants a Krabby Patty?

09:39.744 --> 09:42.278
- Oh, we've got plenty
of Krabby Patties

09:42.280 --> 09:45.315
right here in the freezer.

09:47.384 --> 09:49.252
[microwave whirring]

09:49.254 --> 09:50.219
- Ding.

09:50.221 --> 09:50.920
- You see?

09:50.922 --> 09:54.924
Customers at the museum can
cook the patties themselves,

09:54.926 --> 09:55.758
like this.

09:55.760 --> 09:57.994
[humming, chomping]

10:00.264 --> 10:03.766
Yeah, it's so convenient, see?
[chuckles]

10:03.768 --> 10:05.268
- And what about me?

10:05.270 --> 10:08.705
- Don't worry, Squidward.
You're fired.

10:08.707 --> 10:12.342
- Well, do I get re-hired
for a new job at the museum too?

10:12.344 --> 10:14.143
- Heh!
No, you're just fired.

10:14.145 --> 10:17.280
- What?
No, you don't fire me--I quit.

10:17.282 --> 10:19.315
I got my resignation letter
all prepared.

10:19.317 --> 10:22.151
"Dear Mr. Krabs--"
- Do you have a ticket, sir?

10:22.153 --> 10:23.820
Can't be in a museum
without a ticket.

10:23.822 --> 10:27.490
- What the--what?
"I-I-I tender my resignation

10:27.492 --> 10:29.826
"from this greasy establishment.

10:29.828 --> 10:31.761
"Too long have I toiled

10:31.763 --> 10:33.062
"under your iron claw.

10:33.064 --> 10:35.198
"Now I am free--free to live

10:35.200 --> 10:37.800
"my dreams of being
a ballet dancer, ha-ha,

10:37.802 --> 10:41.771
"and the first chair clarinet
in the Bikini Bottom Orchestra,

10:41.773 --> 10:44.974
"ha-ha, and I am going to
finally publish

10:44.976 --> 10:51.781
my mystery/thriller novel:
'Dial D for Doily'!"

10:51.783 --> 10:53.816
<i>[quirky music]</i>

10:53.818 --> 10:54.517
- Ooh.

10:54.519 --> 10:55.852
[all murmuring]

10:55.854 --> 10:59.856
- Ahem, "hello, and welcome to
the Krusty Krab Museum,

10:59.858 --> 11:01.457
"the original home
of the Krabby Patty,

11:01.459 --> 11:04.027
"now available
in the frozen food section

11:04.029 --> 11:05.862
of your local supermarket."

11:05.864 --> 11:06.429
[bang]

11:06.431 --> 11:10.099
Oh, and don't forget to buy
souvenirs at the gift shop.

11:10.101 --> 11:14.904
- Atta boy, embrace the future!

11:14.906 --> 11:16.506
[clang]

11:16.508 --> 11:20.043
<i>[upbeat orchestral music]</i>

11:20.045 --> 11:27.383
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:29.000 --> 11:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:51.542 --> 11:54.077
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

11:54.079 --> 11:56.546
- [humming]

11:56.548 --> 11:58.247
- Going up?

11:58.249 --> 12:00.550
- I'm going to a party--
a party to celebrate

12:00.552 --> 12:03.186
my friend's upcoming
400th commercial.

12:03.188 --> 12:04.587
- Uh-huh.
- I brought ice cream.

12:04.589 --> 12:07.290
Me and my best friend
are gonna share the ice cream.

12:07.292 --> 12:07.990
Who knows?

12:07.992 --> 12:10.660
Maybe we'll even get
a chance to share pants.

12:10.662 --> 12:12.128
[laughs]

12:12.130 --> 12:13.262
Again.

12:13.264 --> 12:16.666
- You should get out.
Now.

12:17.935 --> 12:19.302
[all murmuring]

12:19.304 --> 12:22.472
- Excuse me, excuse me,
excuse me, pardon me, excuse me.

12:22.474 --> 12:25.608
- Uh, Patrick, did you order
something through the mail?

12:25.610 --> 12:29.212
'Cause a yellow box
just arrived for you.

12:29.214 --> 12:30.246
- SpongeBob!

12:30.248 --> 12:30.980
- Hey, Patrick.

12:30.982 --> 12:34.183
- Oh, I'm sure glad
you made it to my party.

12:34.185 --> 12:37.220
- Uh, excuse me, yellow box,
are you feeling

12:37.222 --> 12:38.087
a little overheated?

12:38.089 --> 12:43.392
Because I do--I say,
I do believe you are melting.

12:43.394 --> 12:44.727
[laughs]

12:44.729 --> 12:46.195
[laughter]

12:46.197 --> 12:49.532
- Oh, yeah, I guess I should
get this in a freezer.

12:49.534 --> 12:51.134
Patrick, where's the kitchen?

12:51.136 --> 12:52.001
- Oh, I don't know.

12:52.003 --> 12:53.236
- It's just past
the solid gold gym.

12:53.238 --> 12:55.605
Take a right at the zoo.
- I'll come with you, SpongeBob.

12:55.607 --> 12:57.473
- He can find the kitchen
by himself.

12:57.475 --> 12:59.075
The press needs
some photos of you

12:59.077 --> 13:01.344
with your new mascot friends.

13:01.346 --> 13:05.014
- Aww.
- Aww.

13:08.519 --> 13:11.487
-<i> [yodeling]</i>

13:11.489 --> 13:15.324
<i>[gloomy music]</i>

13:15.326 --> 13:16.058
- [sighs]

13:16.060 --> 13:18.461
- This way, Mr. Star!
- Hey, Patrick, over here!

13:18.463 --> 13:21.430
- Over here, right here!
- Who are you wearing?

13:23.467 --> 13:25.701
- [sighs]

13:25.703 --> 13:28.237
Whoa, oof!
- Ow.

13:28.239 --> 13:30.173
- Squidward?
What are you doing here?

13:30.175 --> 13:33.209
I thought you were
off following your dreams.

13:33.211 --> 13:33.709
- I was.

13:33.711 --> 13:35.678
They turned out
to be nightmares.

13:35.680 --> 13:38.214
Apparently, you need
more than 17 years

13:38.216 --> 13:42.351
behind a cash register
to be qualified for dreams.

13:42.353 --> 13:43.452
I never thought
I would say this,

13:43.454 --> 13:46.789
but I'm begging you, SpongeBob,
let me come back

13:46.791 --> 13:48.791
and work at
the Krusty Krab Museum.

13:48.793 --> 13:51.294
- I guess you could help out
the animatronic Squidward.

13:51.296 --> 13:53.629
There's something about him
that seems a little off.

13:53.631 --> 13:55.798
- [robotic voice]
I love my job.

13:55.800 --> 13:57.333
Thanks for coming!

13:57.335 --> 14:00.069
- Totally out of character.

14:00.071 --> 14:00.736
[clang]

14:00.738 --> 14:02.538
I hate everyone.

14:02.540 --> 14:04.407
Huh, much better.

14:05.275 --> 14:08.244
- "Tastes so nice that they--"

14:08.246 --> 14:09.745
- They taste like lice!

14:09.747 --> 14:12.114
- Oh, now I gotta start over!

14:12.116 --> 14:15.484
Ooh, someone fix
that broken robot.

14:15.486 --> 14:16.652
- Huh?
Ooh!

14:16.654 --> 14:17.353
[buzzing]

14:17.355 --> 14:18.588
What are you doing with this--
ow!

14:18.590 --> 14:20.389
- "Tastes so nice
that they taste nice."

14:20.391 --> 14:23.726
- Hey, Patrick, rehearsing
your big 400th commercial, huh?

14:23.728 --> 14:27.096
- Excuse me, yellow box,
Mr. Star is not to be disturbed.

14:27.098 --> 14:29.298
He's very, very busy right now.

14:29.300 --> 14:30.633
- Yeah, sure.

14:30.635 --> 14:31.734
I get it.

14:31.736 --> 14:33.302
- But he's my friend.

14:33.304 --> 14:34.237
- You're a star.

14:34.239 --> 14:36.772
You have no friends.

14:37.574 --> 14:38.641
- [sighs]

14:38.643 --> 14:40.142
What am I doing again?

14:40.144 --> 14:43.813
- Stand over here
and say your line.

14:43.815 --> 14:46.582
And...action.

14:46.584 --> 14:49.819
<i>[light music]</i>

14:49.821 --> 14:52.188
- Tastes so nice it...

14:52.190 --> 14:58.728
uh...blah, blah, blah,
blah, bli-blah.

14:58.730 --> 15:00.563
[party favors buzzing]

15:00.565 --> 15:01.230
- And...cut.

15:01.232 --> 15:02.665
All right, you guys
can fix that in post.

15:02.667 --> 15:05.601
Okay, that's a wrap.
Let's pack it up.

15:05.603 --> 15:06.769
- Okay, and here.
And here.

15:06.771 --> 15:08.771
Okay, and then sign here.
And again here.

15:08.773 --> 15:10.373
- Patrick,
there's something weird

15:10.375 --> 15:12.575
about these
Frozen Krabby Patties.

15:12.577 --> 15:15.378
<i>[ominous music]</i>

15:15.380 --> 15:18.581
- Looks like you've been hitting
the patties pretty hard there.

15:18.583 --> 15:20.449
- Speak for yourself.

15:20.451 --> 15:21.684
- Oh, nothing's
been the same

15:21.686 --> 15:24.287
since those frozen patties
came out.

15:24.289 --> 15:26.422
I miss the old Krusty Krab.

15:26.424 --> 15:29.325
I miss Patrick--oof!

15:29.327 --> 15:30.226
- Come on, Mr. Star.

15:30.228 --> 15:33.763
You've got
an 11:00 eyeball waxing.

15:33.765 --> 15:34.864
- [sighs]

15:34.866 --> 15:38.167
See you later, SpongeBob.

15:38.169 --> 15:39.268
- Aww.

15:39.270 --> 15:42.338
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

15:42.340 --> 15:46.742
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:46.744 --> 15:48.844
- [panting]

15:48.846 --> 15:52.581
- Finally, now is
my chance to strike.

15:52.583 --> 15:55.451
- Welcome to
the original Krusty--

15:55.652 --> 15:58.387
- [robotic voice]
Curses, foiled again.

15:58.389 --> 16:00.356
Curses, foiled again.

16:00.358 --> 16:02.758
- Pff, never happened.

16:02.760 --> 16:04.593
[grunts]

16:04.595 --> 16:06.896
Now to make my escape.

16:06.898 --> 16:10.633
[maniacal laughter]

16:11.601 --> 16:13.836
Aren't you gonna
try and stop me?

16:13.838 --> 16:15.905
- That'll be $1.99, please.

16:15.907 --> 16:17.640
- What do you mean, $1.99?

16:17.642 --> 16:18.841
You're not gonna step on me?

16:18.843 --> 16:20.810
I've got the secret formula,
you know.

16:20.812 --> 16:23.579
- Anyone can have
a secret formula.

16:23.581 --> 16:26.816
We sell them in the gift shop.

16:27.417 --> 16:29.251
See?
They're all just fakes.

16:29.253 --> 16:31.687
Everything here is a fake.

16:31.689 --> 16:32.688
- Eh, forget it.

16:32.690 --> 16:34.256
What's the world coming to?

16:34.258 --> 16:37.626
All right, just give me
one Frozen Krabby Patty to go.

16:37.628 --> 16:40.496
- Ding.

16:40.498 --> 16:41.397
- [laughs]

16:41.399 --> 16:42.798
Yes, you fools!

16:42.800 --> 16:44.600
- Shouldn't we chase after him?

16:44.602 --> 16:45.501
He didn't pay.

16:45.503 --> 16:46.435
- Oh, what's the point?

16:46.437 --> 16:50.406
These Frozen Krabby Patties
have ruined my life, Squidward.

16:50.408 --> 16:52.341
And it was all my idea.

16:52.343 --> 16:55.478
Who am I to fight the future?

17:00.283 --> 17:02.618
Blah!

17:02.620 --> 17:03.586
[coughs]

17:03.588 --> 17:04.353
Sand?

17:04.355 --> 17:05.688
It tastes like sand.

17:05.690 --> 17:06.922
Not good sand, either.

17:06.924 --> 17:07.723
- Of course it does.

17:07.724 --> 17:10.326
What do you think
Krabs uses as filler?

17:10.328 --> 17:13.262
- Krabby Patties
aren't made with sand!

17:13.263 --> 17:15.998
They're made with love.

17:16.000 --> 17:17.532
Yah, fwa!

17:17.535 --> 17:18.567
[clang]

17:18.569 --> 17:21.637
<i>[lively music]</i>

17:21.638 --> 17:24.940
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:24.942 --> 17:25.540
Mm!

17:25.542 --> 17:29.245
I am going to show the world
what a fresh, not frozen

17:29.247 --> 17:32.014
Krabby Patty tastes like,
and the first one

17:32.016 --> 17:34.884
is for my best friend, Patrick.

17:35.552 --> 17:38.487
[humming]

17:38.489 --> 17:39.688
[all sniffing]

17:39.690 --> 17:40.689
all: Mmm!

17:40.691 --> 17:41.390
[bubbling]

17:41.392 --> 17:42.792
- Over here.
- Right here, Patrick.

17:42.794 --> 17:44.660
- Right here, right here.
- One, more, Patrick.

17:44.662 --> 17:45.928
- Patrick, baby, sweetheart,

17:45.930 --> 17:47.897
have you thought
about that feature film

17:47.899 --> 17:49.432
I pitched youse?

17:49.434 --> 17:50.299
[all chatting]

17:50.301 --> 17:52.601
[camera shutter clicking]

17:52.603 --> 17:53.536
- That's it.

17:53.538 --> 17:55.471
I can't take it anymore.

17:55.473 --> 17:57.773
Everybody out!

17:57.775 --> 17:59.842
[all grumbling]

17:59.844 --> 18:00.743
[elevator bell dings]

18:00.745 --> 18:05.815
I wish things could go back
to the way they were.

18:05.817 --> 18:07.416
Mm...

18:07.418 --> 18:09.952
I just wanna be able
to share one pair of pants

18:09.954 --> 18:14.056
with my best friend
without it being in the papers.

18:14.058 --> 18:15.825
- Freshly grilled Krabby Patty,

18:15.827 --> 18:18.594
you and I are going to
save the world.

18:18.596 --> 18:21.030
And save a friendship.

18:21.032 --> 18:22.932
Patrick!

18:22.934 --> 18:24.600
- SpongeBob!

18:24.602 --> 18:28.737
- Patrick, the frozen patties
are made with sand!

18:28.739 --> 18:32.007
- SpongeBob, what?

18:32.009 --> 18:32.708
[beeping]

18:32.710 --> 18:35.411
- Patrick,
the Frozen Krabby Patties

18:35.413 --> 18:36.812
are made with sand!

18:36.814 --> 18:41.016
- I thought
they tasted familiar.

18:41.018 --> 18:42.952
[both grunting]

18:42.954 --> 18:44.386
SpongeBob?

18:44.388 --> 18:46.455
[both grunting]

18:46.457 --> 18:48.557
- Missed you.
- I missed you too.

18:48.559 --> 18:51.694
- I got something for you,
from one friend to another.

18:51.696 --> 18:56.398
- No, no, I don't wanna eat
another one of those things!

18:58.835 --> 19:00.936
<i>[orchestral music]</i>

19:00.938 --> 19:02.438
Mm!

19:02.440 --> 19:05.541
Now that's a real Krabby Patty.

19:05.543 --> 19:09.612
Oh, as delicious
as our real friendship.

19:09.614 --> 19:10.980
- Now that we've
saved our friendship,

19:10.982 --> 19:13.516
we have to save the reputation
of the Krabby Patty.

19:13.518 --> 19:17.987
- But I have to speak at
a shareholders meeting tonight.

19:17.989 --> 19:20.856
How am I gonna say nice things
about frozen patties

19:20.858 --> 19:25.027
now that I know
they're filled with sand?

19:25.495 --> 19:27.530
- Well, Patrick,
you're just gonna have to

19:27.532 --> 19:30.766
listen to your heart...
and your stomach.

19:30.768 --> 19:31.467
[bubbling]

19:31.469 --> 19:34.436
- Thank you, everyone,
for coming to this gala event

19:34.438 --> 19:39.875
celebrating the meteoric success
of Frozen Krabby Patties.

19:39.877 --> 19:41.510
In honor of
this momentous occasion,

19:41.512 --> 19:44.880
we are going to premiere
our 400th commercial.

19:44.882 --> 19:47.750
- And here to say a few words
is the face

19:47.752 --> 19:53.422
of the Frozen Krabby Patty,
our own Patrick Star.

19:53.424 --> 19:54.390
Come on up, Patrick!

19:54.392 --> 19:55.224
[cheers and applause]

19:55.226 --> 19:58.627
- I love this guy--I love him!

19:58.629 --> 20:02.798
- Good evening,
ladies and...the other ones.

20:02.800 --> 20:07.436
I know you're all excited
to see the 400th commercial,

20:07.438 --> 20:11.674
but before we see it
I just want to say...

20:11.676 --> 20:14.543
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:14.545 --> 20:18.781
That...that...

20:18.783 --> 20:21.817
Frozen Krabby Patties are...

20:21.819 --> 20:23.686
- Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.

20:23.688 --> 20:25.621
- Made with sand!

20:25.623 --> 20:26.722
[all gasp]

20:26.724 --> 20:27.656
- Oh, no.

20:27.658 --> 20:30.593
- That was cute
when you were rich.

20:30.595 --> 20:31.927
I'm out of here.

20:31.929 --> 20:32.962
[all retching]

20:32.964 --> 20:35.631
- And in shocking news today,
it has been revealed

20:35.633 --> 20:40.436
that Frozen Krabby Patties
are made with sand.

20:40.438 --> 20:42.671
- [retching]

20:42.673 --> 20:45.841
- [retching, coughing]

20:45.843 --> 20:47.509
- [coughing]

20:47.511 --> 20:48.811
- [retching]

20:48.813 --> 20:49.845
- Eee!

20:49.847 --> 20:52.548
- [retching]

20:52.550 --> 20:53.549
- [meows]

20:53.551 --> 20:54.550
- [retching]

20:54.552 --> 20:55.818
- [retching]

20:55.820 --> 20:58.821
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:59.623 --> 21:02.157
- Well, it's gone.
[horn blows]

21:02.159 --> 21:08.230
Everything I spent me life
building is all gone.

21:08.232 --> 21:09.598
I'm ruined.

21:09.600 --> 21:11.767
[sobbing]

21:11.769 --> 21:12.835
What?

21:12.837 --> 21:13.602
- [munching]

21:13.604 --> 21:16.005
Now that's
the taste I remember.

21:16.007 --> 21:17.840
- That's strange.

21:17.842 --> 21:19.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:19.110 --> 21:22.711
Mr. Squidward,
what is going on in here?

21:22.713 --> 21:25.648
- Uh, I am
Animatronic Squidward.

21:25.650 --> 21:27.249
I cannot answer questions.

21:27.251 --> 21:27.916
- Squidward!

21:27.918 --> 21:30.786
- It was SpongeBob's idea.
Him and Patrick are behind this.

21:30.788 --> 21:31.787
They forced me to help.

21:31.789 --> 21:33.756
- ♪ La-la-la-la ♪
- [chuckles]

21:33.758 --> 21:36.792
- SpongeBob,
did you do all this?

21:36.794 --> 21:37.793
- Absolutely!

21:37.795 --> 21:39.762
Well, Patrick helped.

21:39.764 --> 21:41.030
- A friend always helps.

21:41.032 --> 21:46.268
It's called frelping,
and I was very frelpful.

21:46.270 --> 21:49.071
- But how did you
get these customers

21:49.073 --> 21:50.506
to eat Krabby Patties?

21:50.508 --> 21:52.074
They know they're
filled with sand.

21:52.076 --> 21:55.678
- The frozen ones are,
but these are made fresh.

21:55.680 --> 21:56.745
- [gasps]

21:56.747 --> 21:57.579
Fresh?

21:57.581 --> 22:00.149
- Go on, have a bite.

22:00.151 --> 22:01.817
- No, no I--

22:01.819 --> 22:05.754
- Mr. Krabs, just a nibble.

22:05.756 --> 22:07.856
- Mm.

22:07.858 --> 22:09.692
Here!
[munching]

22:09.694 --> 22:14.196
Ooh, hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo,
ooh, the flavor.

22:14.198 --> 22:18.600
The sweet, greasy
nectar of the gods.

22:18.602 --> 22:21.737
How much are you charging
for these patties, boy-o?

22:21.739 --> 22:23.539
- Nothing,
we're not selling them.

22:23.541 --> 22:25.741
- Yeah, we just give them away.

22:25.743 --> 22:28.577
- Agh, SpongeBob, me boy,

22:28.579 --> 22:30.579
you've done a good thing here,
lad,

22:30.581 --> 22:33.849
but you could use
a little frelp, I think.

22:33.851 --> 22:34.717
[grunts]

22:34.719 --> 22:35.984
How about we partner up,

22:35.986 --> 22:36.885
and I become your boss

22:36.887 --> 22:40.956
and pay you minimum wage
while I work you mercilessly?

22:40.958 --> 22:41.757
What do you say?

22:41.759 --> 22:43.692
- Yeah!
The Krusty Krab

22:43.694 --> 22:44.593
is back in business.

22:44.595 --> 22:49.164
- Great, now get to work!
[laughs]

22:51.668 --> 22:54.937
<i>[twangy guitar music]</i>

22:54.939 --> 23:02.244
<i>♪ ♪</i>

